(9, 'PDCS0525001', '21', '15', '0', '1', 'Dunkin\' - San Francisco Pilar', 'Andrew Siruma', '2025-05-28', '13:00:00.000000', '14:30:00.000000', 'CCTV - Digital Video Recorder (DVR)', '1. A beeping sound was reported coming from the CCTV DVR.\r\n2. The CCTV monitor displayed low brightness, making the output nearly unreadable.', '1. Visited the site and brought spare SATA cables and HDD in case replacement was necessary.\r\n2. Performed basic troubleshooting by restarting the DVR (unplugging and replugging the power supply).\r\n3. After rebooting, the beeping sound stopped, indicating temporary resolution without replacing any parts.\r\n4. Checked monitor settings for brightness and contrast â€“ all were at normal levels.\r\n5. Suspected the AC/DC adapter to be the issue.\r\n6. Tested with a spare AC/DC power adapter, and the monitor brightness was restored.', '1. The beeping sound from the DVR was likely a temporary error, possibly related to HDD or power fluctuations.\r\n2. The CCTV monitor\'s dim display was due to a faulty AC/DC power adapter.', '1. Replace the AC/DC power adapter with a new one: 12V/5A PC Monitor Power Supply, 5.5mm x 2.5mm Jack Adapter (60 watts).\r\n2. Continue to monitor the DVR for recurring beeping sounds that may indicate HDD or SATA cable issues.\r\n3. No immediate component replacement required for the DVR as the system is currently functioning properly after restart.', 'Jas Alonzo', 'data:image/png;base64,', NULL, NULL, 'data:image/png;base64,', '2025-05-28 15:47:22.085970', '0000-00-00 00:00:00.000000', '');
